{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"db1d8a44-3244-4181-9e8d-5ee808606a47","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92122697-062c-401a-ae0d-584b73e114ac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly without needing to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":163,"requestId":"5C5D:2CDF90:1FF54C:27A198:69F55105"},"id":"2c9838e4-7a2e-4c65-be9d-6f50396d3c89","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:19:06.131Z","parentId":"e1e8af61-22b8-4af7-a15a-1c7aee4acd24"}
